snippet: An agreement to defuse a strike by Chinese journalists had been reached by early Wednesday, although several reporters said the deal could fall apart.
abstract: Tentative deal is reached between striking Chinese journalists and newspaper Southern Weekend, which has been accused by journalists of censorship; some reporters are told that paper will publish as usual on Thursday.

byline.original: By EDWARD WONG and CHRIS BUCKLEY
byline.contributor: Edward Wong reported from Guangzhou, and Chris Buckley from Hong Kong. Jonah M. Kessel contributed reporting from Guangzhou, and Jonathan Ansfield from Beijing. Mia Li contributed research from Guangzhou.

lead_paragraph: An agreement to defuse a strike by Chinese journalists had been reached by early Wednesday, although several reporters said the deal could fall apart.

headline.seo: Tentative Deal Reported in Chinese Censorship Dispute
headline.main: Tentative Deal Reported in Chinese Censorship Dispute
headline.print_headline: Tentative Deal Is Reached With Journalists Protesting Censorship at Chinese Newspaper
